Iran defended its decision to use faster centrifuges prohibited by its 2015 nuclear deal with world powers, officials said Sunday, while underscoring that time was running out for Europe to save the unraveling accord. Iran already has crept past limits the deal imposed on nuclear enrichment and its uranium stockpile. It is trying to pressure Europe to find a way to sell crude oil abroad despite U.S. sanctions, Starts and Stripes reports. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif claimed Iran’s announcement the day before that it would use advanced centrifuges was still within the “framework” of the 2015 nuclear deal, while meeting with the visiting acting chief of the U.N. atomic watchdog Cornel Feruta. 